    "paragraphs": [
        "",
        "Advance your career in the dynamic and ever-changing world of information security, cyber threats and cybercrime investigation.",
        "Department of Security Studies and Criminal Justice",
        "According to the FBI, the cybercrime threat by criminals, overseas adversaries and terrorists is incredibly serious and growing. And, ZipRecruiter reports that the average salary for cybercrime investigators in the U.S. is about $100,000 per year.",
        "Note: Applications not meeting GPA requirements will be viewed on a case-by-case basis by the department chair.",
        "This graduate-level certificate program consists of 12 credit hours. That means you only have to complete four courses to earn your certificate.",
        "Once you earn your certificate, you can also apply the credits toward an online Master of Science in criminal justice degree right here at Angelo State.",
        "Our graduate certificate program is the first of its kind in Texas offered through a criminal justice program rather than a computer science program.",
        "Total Credit Hours: 12",
        "Certificate Advisor",
        "If you want to go fast, go alone. But if you want to go far, go together.",
